cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.PR 

The paper discusses user attitudes towards TLS inspection, which is a security and privacy issue. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also touches on issues related to cyber threats and government surveillance, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society). The survey methodology and data analysis could be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses user behavior and privacy concerns, which could be relevant to cs.PR (Privacy and Security).
